The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the coloring of point sets in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves range spaces, which are often studied in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The use of colors and the concept of homothetic copies suggest a connection to Combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of a bound suggests a connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT).
